CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 11, 1961, pg. 1, reads: "Henry Ryan Makes History - Thirteenth Ward Democratic aldermanic winner Henry Ryan (in trench coat), made history in Tuesday's election, when he became the first Negro ever elected alderman of that ward.  He waged a good fight and won easily over his GOP opponent, Daniel Gaitinelli, 4, 010 votes to 1,864.  Ryan is shown with some of his supporters in the 11th District.  The rumored 'Rebel' uprising failed to materialize, and regular party-endorsed candidates won."
TitMainTitle: Women and men gathered around alderman candidate Henry Ryan wearing light colored trench coat and eyeglasses, outside polling place
